    "section_QNR88H": {
      "type": "section",
      "blocks": {
        "text_9CHVLe": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Watching Episode 1 Stab In The Dark with Ethan Ewing got us so stoked. It was a “maybe” for a long time. Getting Ethan locked in came with so many what ifs? We got it pretty easy, but could still feel the angst as the details came together. The boards were flown in from two places, so we pulled a team coffin from CREATURES USA and one from here in Oz. We added heaps of Ethan’s go-to traction, leashes, a few Day Use bags, some board socks, and more to properly support Eth with his insane quiver of blue-railed beauties. </p><p>The location was confirmed and tickets bought. Once the planes left, and we got confirmation the gear was in the plane’s belly, things went silent. The first email updates came in from the Stab crew, including the odd frame grab. Anticipation began to mount. That was months ago. </p><p>The wait was worth it. </p><p>Episode 1 was so damn entertaining. Ethan’s that good he can get 9s sitting down.</p><p>Live now on <a href=\"https://stabmag.com/\" title=\"https://stabmag.com/\">Stab Premium</a>.</p><p>Check the unseen footage below.</p>",
            "width": "100%",
            "max_width": "none",
            "alignment": "center",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
